Step 1: Identify the quick assets on the balance sheet. These include:
• Cash on Hand = 5,603,438.00  
• Bank Deposits = 3,642,142.45  
• Interest Receivable = 10,710.07  
• Accounts Receivable = 1,355,463.34  

Step 2: Sum these quick assets.  
Quick Assets = 5,603,438.00 + 3,642,142.45 + 10,710.07 + 1,355,463.34 = 10,611,753.86

Step 3: Note the Total Current Liabilities on the balance sheet which is given as 2,110,671.05.

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio using the formula:  
Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities = 10,611,753.86 / 2,110,671.05 ≈ 5.03

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "5.03"
  }
}
